answers.body_markdown:
`row_number()` is a typical solution:

    select t.*
    from (select t.*,
                 row_number() over (partition by WebAppUserName order by datecol) as seqnum
          from t
         ) t
    where seqnum = 1;

Often a correlated subquery has the good performance:

    select t.*
    from t
    where t.datecol = (select min(t2.datecol)
                       from t t2
                       where t2.WebAppUserName = t.WebAppUserName
                      );

